on and psyche. The attack on the Lusitania, he argues, was not simply an escalation of violence but signaled a new ideological, moral, and religious dimension in the struggle between German Kultur and Western civilization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xNaval operationsxSubmarine. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh1 aSpencer, Stewart08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224245423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224245.jpg  a978-3-11-066771-4  YUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles